nsition-colors" href="mailto:hello@bolt.build">hello@bolt.build</a><a class="text-current font-body text-xl block hover:text-yellow transition-colors" href="tel:+1 917-740-3463">+1 917-740-3463</a></div></div></div></div><div class="col-span-2 lg:col-span-1 border-t-0 lg:border-t border-x md:border-x-0 border-current"></div></div></div><div class="absolute inset-0 -z-10"><div class="cover-image-shim absolute inset-0 z-10"></div><img src="https://www.boltdesign.nyc/_next/image?url=https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.sanity.io%2Fimages%2F4j6lg3tu%2Fproduction%2F6f74a9fd05606826b72b4f7a4fe9138829e55af2-1920x1080.png&amp;w=3840&amp;q=75" srcSet="https://www.boltdesign.nyc/_next/image?url=https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.sanity.io%2Fimages%2F4j6lg3tu%2Fproduction%2F6f74a9fd05606826b72b4f7a4fe9138829e55af2-1920x1080.png&w=1920&q=75amp;qhttps://www.boltdesign.nyc/_next/image?url=https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.sanity.io%2Fimages%2F4j6lg3tu%2Fproduction%2F6f74a9fd05606826b72b4f7a4fe9138829e55af2-1920x1080.png&w=3840&q=75;w=3840&amp;q=75 2x" alt="" width="1920" height="1080" class="absolute object-cover w-full h-full z-0 inset-0" loading="lazy" sizes="(max-width: 600px) 300vw, (max-width: 1000px) 200vw, 100vw"/></div><div class="border-x flex-1 flex flex-col justify-end"></div></header><div class="z-20 relative bg-white"><div class="sticky top-0 invisible"><div class="px-unit absolute left-0 right-0 bg-white"><div class="pt-unit border-black border-b"></div></div></div><div class="px-unit"><div class="pt-unit border-black border-x"><div class="sticky top-unit"><div class="grid grid-cols-12 gap-unit px-unit pt-2 pb-4"><div class="col-span-6 lg:col-span-3 pr-2"><p class="text-current font-body text-3xl">Matter of Design | Breeze Blocks </p></div><div class="col-span-6 lg:col-span-2"><h3 class="text-current font-body text-md">July 8, 2025</h3></div></div></div><div class="grid grid-cols-12 gap-unit px-unit pt-8 pb-unit"><div class="col-start-1 col-end-13 md:col-start-2 md:col-end-12 lg:col-start-4 lg:col-end-12 xl:col-start-4 xl:col-end-10"><p class="text-current font-body text-xl mt-12 first:mt-0 mb-4 font-medium">Breeze Blocks</p><p class="text-current font-body text-md mb-4"><br/>From raw origins to refined forms, we spotlight the materials that shape how we build, live, and experience spaces.</p><div class="mt-12 mb-8 w-full"><img src="https://www.boltdesign.nyc/_next/image?url=https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.sanity.io%2Fimages%2F4j6lg3tu%2Fproduction%2F2fe2736c44ecda8cdfe78798f77c408ee835c414-1920x1080.png&amp;w=3840&amp;q=75" srcSet="https://www.boltdesign.nyc/_next/image?url=https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.sanity.io%2Fimages%2F4j6lg3tu%2Fproduction%2F2fe2736c44ecda8cdfe78798f77c408ee835c414-1920x1080.png&w=1920&q=75amp;qhttps://www.boltdesign.nyc/_next/image?url=https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.sanity.io%2Fimages%2F4j6lg3tu%2Fproduction%2F2fe2736c44ecda8cdfe78798f77c408ee835c414-1920x1080.png&w=3840&q=75;w=3840&amp;q=75 2x" alt="breeze blocks bolt builds " width="1920" height="1080" loading="lazy"/></div><p class="text-current font-body text-md mb-4">These patterned decorative blocks made of concrete or clay became popular in the 1950s and ’60s Mid-Century Modern era. Used on walls and facades, they provide shade, airflow, privacy, and protection. All while adding stylish geometric patterns, especially suited to warmer climates.</p><div class="mt-12 mb-8 w-full"><img src="https://www.boltdesign.nyc/_next/image?url=https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.sanity.io%2Fimages%2F4j6lg3tu%2Fproduction%2F32ab7746ef01cf8cb0fe82905378ddbf52e9528b-1000x563.jpg&amp;w=2048&amp;q=75" srcSet="https://www.boltdesign.nyc/_next/image?url=https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.sanity.io%2Fimages%2F4j6lg3tu%2Fproduction%2F32ab7746ef01cf8cb0fe82905378ddbf52e9528b-1000x563.jpg&w=1080&q=75amp;qhttps://www.boltdesign.nyc/_next/image?url=https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.sanity.io%2Fimages%2F4j6lg3tu%2Fproduction%2F32ab7746ef01cf8cb0fe82905378ddbf52e9528b-1000x563.jpg&w=2048&q=75;w=2048&amp;q=75 2x" alt="breeze blocks tamara wibowo architects " width="1000" height="563" loading="lazy"/></div><p class="text-current font-body text-md mb-4">Breeze Blocks House by Tamara Wibowo Architects uses breeze blocks as a defining feature, shaping both the exterior and interior of the home. These patterned blocks create natural ventilation and filtered light throughout the space, enhancing comfort while adding distinctive texture and privacy. The design celebrates the material’s functional beauty, seamlessly blending openness with shelter in a modern, thoughtful way.</p><p class="text-current font-body text-md mb-4"></p><div class="mt-12 mb-8 w-full"><img src="https://www.boltdesign.nyc/_next/image?url=https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.sanity.io%2Fimages%2F4j6lg3tu%2Fproduction%2F7ce9a3446238bc9c3e255ae7afed60a3a1090e97-810x1080.jpg&amp;w=1920&amp;q=75" srcSet="https://www.boltdesign.nyc/_next/image?url=https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.sanity.io%2Fimages%2F4j6lg3tu%2Fproduction%2F7ce9a3446238bc9c3e255ae7afed60a3a1090e97-810x1080.jpg&w=828&q=75amp;qhttps://www.boltdesign.nyc/_next/image?url=https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.sanity.io%2Fimages%2F4j6lg3tu%2Fproduction%2F7ce9a3446238bc9c3e255ae7afed60a3a1090e97-810x1080.jpg&w=1920&q=75;w=1920&amp;q=75 2x" alt="Breeze Blocks House Tamara Wibowo Architects" width="810" height="1080" loading="lazy"/></div><p class="text-current font-body text-md mb-4"></p><div class="mt-12 mb-8 w-full"><img src="https://www.boltdesign.nyc/_next/image?url=https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.sanity.io%2Fimages%2F4j6lg3tu%2Fproduction%2F3a689812c0ac099cf607a508d90508a69e253e4e-2132x1199.jpg&amp;w=3840&amp;q=75" srcSet="https://www.boltdesign.nyc/_next/image?url=https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.sanity.io%2Fimages%2F4j6lg3tu%2Fproduction%2F3a689812c0ac099cf607a508d90508a69e253e4e-2132x1199.jpg&w=3840&q=75amp;q=75 1x" alt="Inca Hernández Arquitectura Breeze Blocks" width="2132" height="1199" loading="lazy"/></div><p class="text-current font-body text-md mb-4">Mar Mediterráneo 34 in Mexico City, restored by Inca Hernández Arquitectura, brings new life to a 1910 house by preserving original details like the façade and balconies. The project introduces patios with breeze blocks that allow natural light and airflow while providing privacy and texture. This thoughtful use of the material creates a perfect balance between historic charm and breathable, inviting spaces.<br/><br/></p><div class="mt-12 mb-8 w-full"><img src="https://www.boltdesign.nyc/_next/image?url=https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.sanity.io%2Fimages%2F4j6lg3tu%2Fproduction%2F70749ccb3630a7baf33a6b5d009528f212764fca-1333x2000.jpg&amp;w=3840&amp;q=75" srcSet="https://www.boltdesign.nyc/_next/image?url=https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.sanity.io%2Fimages%2F4j6lg3tu%2Fproduction%2F70749ccb3630a7baf33a6b5d009528f212764fca-1333x2000.jpg&w=1920&q=75amp;qhttps://www.boltdesign.nyc/_next/image?url=https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.sanity.io%2Fimages%2F4j6lg3tu%2Fproduction%2F70749ccb3630a7baf33a6b5d009528f212764fca-1333x2000.jpg&w=3840&q=75;w=3840&amp;q=75 2x" alt="Inca Hernández Arquitectura Breeze Blocks" width="1333" height="2000" loading="lazy"/></div><div class="mt-16"><div class="flex flex-col items-center justify-center pt-6 pb-8"><div><p class="text-current font-body text-xl text-black mx-auto text-center max-w-[420px]">Subscribe to our newsletter to get the latest updates, insights, and articles from our team.</p><div class="mt-4 text-center"><div class="border-black border inline-block"><form class="flex items-center justify-between"><input type="email" placeholder="Email" class="bg-white px-5 py-4 rounded-none focus:outline-none hover:bg-diminished flex-1" value=""/><button type="submit" class="min-w-[160px] px-5 py-4 bg-black text-white hover:bg-blue transition-colors">Subscribe</button></form></div></div></div></div></div></div></div><div class="grid grid-cols-12 gap-unit px-unit pt-8 pb-unit flex justify-between"><a class="col-span-3 hover:opacity-60 transition-opacity" href="../insights"><p class="text-current font-body text-md">Return to Insights List</p><p class="text-current font-body text-xl">←</p></a><a class="col-start-10 col-span-3 text-right hover:opacity-60 transiti